sequenceDiagram
    participant SWIM as SwimActor<br/>(any live node)
    participant MR as MultiRaftActor<br/>(on shard group's leader)
    participant L as Raft Leader<br/>(state machine)
    participant F1 as Raft Follower 1
    participant F2 as Raft Follower 2

    Note over SWIM,F2: Node n3 dies. SWIM detects after ~6-7s (probe + suspect + confirm).

    SWIM->>MR: HandleNodeDeath { dead: n3, live: [n1, n2] }

    Note over MR: For each group where<br/>n3 ∈ peers && raft.is_leader():

    MR->>L: propose(RaftCommand::RemovePeer(n3))
    L->>L: append log[k] = RemovePeer(n3)<br/>peers UNCHANGED until apply

    par replicate
        L->>F1: AppendEntries { entries: [log[k]] }
        F1->>F1: append log[k]<br/>peers UNCHANGED
        F1-->>L: ack k
    and
        L->>F2: AppendEntries { entries: [log[k]] }
        F2->>F2: append log[k]<br/>peers UNCHANGED
        F2-->>L: ack k
    end

    Note over L: majority ack → commit_index = k
    L->>L: apply_remove_peer(n3):<br/>peers -= {n3}<br/>peer_states -= {n3}

    par commit advance
        L->>F1: AppendEntries (heartbeat, commit=k)
        F1->>F1: apply_remove_peer(n3):<br/>peers -= {n3}
    and
        L->>F2: AppendEntries (heartbeat, commit=k)
        F2->>F2: apply_remove_peer(n3):<br/>peers -= {n3}
    end

    Note over L,F2: All replicas now agree on peer set<br/>at log index k. Quorum math safe.

    Note over SWIM,F2: HandleNodeJoin is symmetric:<br/>leader proposes AddPeer(new_node);<br/>followers apply on commit.

    Note over SWIM,F2: Leader-election reconciliation:<br/>on becoming leader, scan peers vs SWIM live set,<br/>propose RemovePeer for any peer SWIM considers dead.
